<br>
The business administration student society held a corporate fair where reps from various companies were invited to set up booths and inform students about their products, services and of course, prospective employment.<br>
<br>
As a member of the student body council, I had to do my turn at manning our booth, when an extremely attractive woman walks up.  Another fellow manning the booth greeted her very pleasantly and her response was:<br>
<br>
&quot;Who is responsible for this corporate monstrosity?!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
The president of the business administration student society was in earshot so he steps up and begins chatting with this extremely agitated woman who goes on and on about a university campus not being an appropriate platform for corporate advertising.<br>
<br>
Then she went on about how offended she was about the Schneider's booth, what with them cooking hotdogs, smokies and other meat products that everyone was forced to smell - including die hard vegans such as herself.  At this point she was very loud, and being an anti-corporate, anti-establishment, vegan, she probably thought this was her moment to shine.<br>
<br>
Being a rather astute fellow, and a total ass, the business admin student body president then asked her in voice as loud as hers, something to the effect of:<br>
<br>
&quot;So you are against the exploitation of animals for corporate or consumer gain?&quot;<br>
<br>
She responded:  &quot;Yes.  All of you should.&quot;<br>
<br>
To which he responded:  &quot;So what type of plant did you get your suede jacket, leather boots and leather handbag from?&quot;<br>
<br>
/bonk.  That was ownage.<br>
<br>
Now, I'm not slandering anti-corporate, anti-establishment and/or vegetarians/vegans...but this thread just reminded me of this funny and hypocritic story. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukathatlafv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KathatlaFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/20/02 5:42:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1430.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_supermad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Vegans can eat me!</span><hr size=1> Although in theory it *IS* healthier to be a veget. most people forget a few things.  Many of the &quot;fake meat&quot; products contain lots of artificial junk as well, which is what a lot of vegetarians are trying to get away from (hormones, antibiotics etc in beef are what some people try and get away from anyway)...  Too much soy can be bad for you as well.  As for myself, i'm not a big meat eater and generally wont order beef, etc, at a restraunt, but a little Venison or smoked salmon is delicious (I live in AK) <p>Woos-Troll Shaman-Firiona Vie-Ebon Storm
