<br>
Humans are meant to be omnivores, like bears.<br>
<br>
Pregnant women need to eat meat for fetus's to develop properly. Studies have been done, that show that a strict vegetarian diet is very bad for nursing babies, because they are not getting the protiens they need from the mother. The babies do not grow in weight or intelligence, in comparison to babies of the same age born to omnivourous mothers.<br>
<br>
If you believe in Darwinism, vegetarians will all go the way of the dinosaurs...eventually.<br>
<br>
Other than that, if you don't want to eat meat, don't. I'm not going to stop you, but don't try to stop me.<br>
<br>
And yes, wild game (moose, deer, grouse) is better for you than farm raised meat. It is leaner, and has more protein per ounce.<br>
<br>
And yes, moose is the best tasting meat I have ever had. A nice roast, slowly cooked over a fire for 4 hours...mmmm<br>
<br>
