<br>
I do not look down on those who eat meat.  We all make our own decisions.<br>
<br>
I chose to go vegetarian because I can not bring about the suffering of another living thing.<br>
<br>
Do plants truely feel?  If they do, the current scientific literature does not say so.  And if they do, is it really on the scale of a cow, a sentient living being?<br>
<br>
Hunting your own meat is one thing.  The death camps that the meat industry run are another.  <br>
<br>
But still, I will never criticize anyone for eating meat.<br>
<br>
What I will criticize are those who argue for the right to life of every human being, whether just concieved or at 8 months , yet still continue to support the meat industry.<br>
<br>
<br>
A cow suffers much more than any fetus.  A cow has a fully developed nervous system.  To argue that a clump of cells has more rights against suffering that a fuly developed life form is to treat humans as a separate species, unconnected to all others in the animal kingdom, and to ignore the last 100 plus years of biological research.<br>
<br>
We are animals.  <br>
<br>
Looking back at that, I can feel the flames coming in.<br>
<br>
Anyway, the truth of the matter is that Meat IS still murder, and dairy IS still rape.<br>
<br>
If your concious can deal with the fact, then I am not going to argue your meat eating tendacies.<br>
<br>
As for myself, I feel that &quot;Life is too short to make others shorter.&quot;-Prophaghandi<br>
<br>
<br>
